## Step 4 — Use in your app
```js
const { getCredentials, getServiceCredentials } = require('./ganson');

// Load ALL keys for this client
const creds = await getCredentials();

// Use individual keys
const anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: creds.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY });
const twilio    = require('twilio')(creds.TWILIO_SID, creds.TWILIO_TOKEN);

// Load keys for one service only
const twilioKeys = await getServiceCredentials('twilio');
```

---

## Step 5 — Test the connection
```bash
# Quick curl test (replace PASSWORD and SLUG)
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $(echo -n 'PASSWORD:gansonstreet' | base64)" \
  "https://admin.gansonstreet.com/api/credentials/SLUG"
```

---

## Step 6 — Adding new keys to a client
1. Log into **https://admin.gansonstreet.com**
2. Find the client (mario, bnmc, ganson)
3. Add new key/value pair
4. Call `getCredentials()` in your app — new key is instantly available, no redeploy needed

